  "texts": [
    "Rule-based techniques, formulated before trained generative algorithms, provide a structured approach to exploring the chemical space.",
    "Combinatorial chemistry principles are used to construct a well-defined chemical space and a set of traversal rules for these techniques.",
    "Combinatorial chemistry involves the creation of molecules by combining molecular substructures or atoms based on human-defined rules.",
    "These methodologies differ according to the rules employed in the combinatorial process and the exploratory algorithms used to select molecules to analyze from these potentially extensive sets.",
    "The chemical space can be defined in several ways:"
  ]
